        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} was born at term via normal vaginal delivery with no perinatal complications. She has been generally healthy, meeting all developmental milestones, and received all recommended childhood vaccinations. She had two prior episodes of mild pharyngitis at ages 6 and 7, both managed with rest and analgesics without antibiotic treatment, and both resolved within a week. There is no prior history of hospitalisation, peritonsillar abscess, or scarlet fever. {patientName} lives in a suburban home with her parents and 6-year-old brother. She attends a school with a recent cluster of streptococcal throat infections among her classmates, raising her exposure risk. She has no known chronic illnesses, no surgical history, and takes no regular medications. Her only documented allergy is to penicillin (urticaria). Diet is balanced; she has no tobacco smoke exposure at home."
          }
        ]
      }
